19/11/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- Border police at a checkpoint in Edrine province seized 575kg of heroin Monday (November 17th) hidden in a truck. The vehicle, owned by the Bafralilar Nakliyat company, was carrying steel drills and cases from Istanbul, apparently destined for EU member countries. Police arrested the driver. (Vecer - 19/11/08; Makfax - 18/11/08; Haber, Milliyet, Zaman, RIA Novosti - 17/11/08)
